Reasoning: The paper discusses the use of deep learning algorithms for image segmentation in medical analysis, specifically for identifying cells' nuclei. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of fully convolutional neural networks (FCNs), which is a popular technique in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The evaluation of the method on a dataset suggests information retrieval (cs.IR) as another possible sub-category. Finally, the use of neural networks implies the involvement of neural networks (cs.NE) as well.
